tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Additional Qualifying Tournament Finisher or Finished 76-100 on 2015 Web.com Tour Money List
tourBios.curYearHigh: Played in 21 Web.com Tour events, making 11 cuts. Had three top 25s and finished 92nd on the money list...Top performances were a T11 at the Utah Championship in August and a T13 at the Rust-Oleum Championship in July...Recorded two eagles in the same round (first) at the Cartagena de Indias at Karibana Championship.
tourBios.carHigh:
2014: In his Web.com Tour rookie season, played in 23 tournaments and made nine cuts. Finished 67th on the money list. Best performance came at the Mexico Championship, where he was T3...Two events later, he posted his second top-10, a T8, at the South Georgia Classic 

2013: Made one cut in three Web.com Tour starts. Best week was a T15 at the Air Capital Classic...Made seven cuts in nine starts on PGA TOUR Canada and had five top-25 finishes. Finished 12th on the Order of Merit. Best week was a runner-up showing at The Players Cup...Was also T5 at the Tour Championship...Was medalist in his second stage qualifier in Plantation, Fla., at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament, posting a 21-under total, which included a 63 in the third round.

2012: Missed the cut at the WNB Golf Classic. 

2011: Finished T41 at the Soboba Golf Classic.

2010: Made two cuts in five Web.com Tour starts. Only top-25 was a T23 at the Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open...On the PGA TOUR, missed the cut at the Farmers Insurance Open outside San Diego. 

2009: Missed the cut the U.S. Open after qualifying. 

2008: Was T47 at the Price Cutter Charity Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Named Player of the Year three times during his high school career. Named to the All-Pac-10 team at Arizona.
tourBios.personal: Attended Sabino High School in Tucson...Favorite courses he's played are Bandon Dunes in Oregon and Bethpage State Park's Black Course. Would like to play St. Andrews...Favorite teams growing up were, and still are, the Dallas Cowboys and Houston Astros. Favorite college team is the University of Arizona...Carries beef jerky in his bag as a snack...Would like to trade places with the President of the United States for a day...Would include Lee Trevino and Chi Chi Rodriguez in his dream foursome.
